Sweden Defeats Australia 3-1 to Reach Semifinals of Women’s World Cup

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-07-10T13:21:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/sweden-defeats-australia-3-1-to-reach-semifinals-of-women-s-world-cup.html
Sweden advanced to the semifinals of
soccer’s Women’s World Cup with a 3-1 win against  Australia 
today in Augsburg,  Germany .  Therese Sjogran, Lisa Dahlkvist and Lotta Schelin scored
for the 2003 runnerup, which will face  Japan  in the last four on
July 13.  Ellyse Perry was the goalscorer for Australia, which
matched its previous best performance of reaching the
quarterfinals in 2007.  The U.S., a  two-time champion , faces  Brazil  in today’s
other quarterfinal in Dresden. The U.S. has never failed to
reach at least the semifinals.  Yesterday, two-time defending champion Germany was beaten
by Japan 1-0 in extra time, while  France  advanced in a penalty
shootout against  England . France won the shootout 4-3 following
a 1-1 tie after extra time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in  London  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 